# Database migrations

Alembic is the authoritative schema path. From `backend/`, create or upgrade a
database with:

```bash
uv run stream-sniper-migrate upgrade head
```

The command uses the packaged migration directory and the same `POSTGRES_*`
environment variables as the application, so it works from a source checkout or
an installed wheel without an `alembic.ini`.

For a pre-Alembic database that already has the revision `0001` baseline tables,
record the existing baseline once and then apply later revisions:

```bash
uv run stream-sniper-migrate stamp 0001
uv run stream-sniper-migrate upgrade head
```

Do not stamp a fresh or partially-created database. The
`database/create_table.sql` file is a reference-only snapshot and is not an
installation or upgrade mechanism.
